# Ninja Agents

A shared playground for AI agents that help engineering teams. Each agent is self-contained under `agents/`.

## Available Workflows

Invoke these by name (e.g., `@weekly-team-update`) or describe what you need:

| Rule                    | Purpose                                                        |
| ----------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `@weekly-team-update`   | Weekly team report for leadership (GitHub + GitLab + Jira)     |
| `@sprint-retro`         | Sprint retrospective analysis from active Jira sprint          |
| `@repo-contextification`| Audit repo docs and scaffold missing files                     |

Each rule points to its full workflow in `.claude/agents/{name}.md` — the single source of truth.

## MCP Servers

Configured in `.cursor/mcp.json`. Tokens from environment variables:

- **GitHub MCP** — `GITHUB_PAT`
- **GitLab MCP** — `GITLAB_PAT` (gitlab.cee.redhat.com)
- **Atlassian Rovo MCP** — browser OAuth (redhat.atlassian.net)

## Key Conventions

- Only `resolution = "Done"` counts as a completed Jira deliverable
- GitLab queries MUST include `scope: "all"` or results may be empty
- All report links use markdown hyperlinks with descriptive text
- CSV fields containing commas must be wrapped in double quotes
- Never commit tokens or secrets

## Contributing

See `agents/_template/README.md` for the expected structure when adding a new agent.
